The '''Mahtam''' are a clan found among the [[Punjabi people|Punjabis]] of [[India]] and [[Pakistan]]. They practice [[Hindu]], [[Sikh]] and [[Muslim]] religions.
During [[British rule in India]], they were stigmatized under the [[Criminal Tribes Act]] 1871.<ref name=jai>[http://dsal.uchicago.edu/reference/gazetteer/pager.html?objectid=DS405.1.I34_V20_369.gif Punjab - Police and Jails] ''[[The Imperial Gazetteer of India]]'', 1908, v. 20, ''p. 363.''</ref>
