{{Sikh scriptures}}
'''Sawaiya''' is a form of poetry which is written in praise of someone in which every verse is one and quarter times the length of common verse.<ref>{{cite book |last=Narang |first=Sampuran Singh |date=2003 |title=The Evening Prayers Rahras Sahib and Kirtan Sohila|url= |location= |publisher=Hemkunt Press|page=152|isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref> The plural of Savaiya is '''Savaiye'''. Famous among them are [[Tav-Prasad Savaiye]], [[33 Savaiye]], [[Bhattan De Savaiye]].

